result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeremy J Cynor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Sexual Contact, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Jeremy J Cynor in court with attorney James H Krave.  James D Babbitt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls PSI writer, unable to reach via telephone.  Parties wish to proceed with sentencing.  Plea entered on count 3 in error, corrected this day.  Sabrina Niles wishes to make a statement to the court in support of Mr Cynor.  Argument entered by the State, state recommends the lower end of the PSI recommendations.  Atty Krave enters argument, asking for waiver of conditional jail time, or time shorten.  Mr Cynor makes a statement to the court, realizes his error, has moved forward in life.  10:30- PSI author calls the courtroom.  Court asks if recommendations would change w/o Ct 3 as a guilty plea.  Court will order sentence withheld, 4 years probation, 6 months jail, stayed, will register for sex offender registry, CC, DNA sample and surcharge, will comply with all recommendations of DOC agent.
